/* Box-model rules shared by the inner button of a restructured row
   (`.room-row__main`) and the flat "create room" row, which has no inner
   button and so still needs them directly. */

/* Active room: the row background is --block-bg (= --orange in dark), so the
   default orange badge vanishes against it. Recolor against the row bg via the
   purpose-built --room-active-count-bg token (dark bg in dark, orange in light). */

/* The room row sits on a dark media background, so a light translucent fill
     + outline read clearly. --active/--danger override with solid orange/red
     below (they come later, so the base loses without needing a :not()). */

/* Self voice active: the compact input-mode icon greens (online-status style).
   Only sets color (the lucide icon is currentColor) — defined after the base so
   it wins without touching the button's bg/border fill. */

/* Speaking cue for tiles showing video content (camera on) or for screen-sharers: an
   accent border + glow on the tile frame, riding the existing .tile border/box-shadow
   transition. Voice-only tiles use the avatar ring above instead, not this frame. */

/* Drag handle on the chat panel's grid-facing edge (left when docked right,
   right when docked left) — resizes the chat panel width. Wider invisible hit
   area; the visible highlight is the thin `::after` line at the grid-facing edge. */
